2rmfH5FcIa6J9KgruYn09oDFTzk\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting lifecycle events**\\n\\nIt looks like I'm checking the interaction between lifecycle events and the user configuration. The existing setup doesn't require any changes, but I wonder if using the JUnit Jupiter API might affect how parameters are handled. There's also the concern of listener order when the host starts. I contemplate if it’s acceptable to invoke a listener with a manufactured lifecycle event as a public API. It feels better to add it directly to the host to ensure proper event triggering. Let's ensure the state transitions rightly after the startInternal process.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing host state transitions**\\n\\nI'm considering the scenario where `host.addChild` is called during the start event while the state is STARTING. I think using `getState().isAvailable` could potentially return true in this case, though `startChildren` would still be false. It's more public to use `host.addLifecycleListener(userConfig)` before starting. I should prepare `userConfig` properly so that when `host.start` receives `UserConfig.start`, it can deploy and add the child. Plus, I need to ensure that we handle the stop or destroy processes appropriately. What about the `catalinaBase` settings?\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_NeqvuPdmKTE5PcMuAzunO7et|fc_06093e8c5a67ae81016a35295bee64819091b41b43f791a598", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-core/11.0.18/src/test/java/tomcat/UserConfigTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage tomcat;\n\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.util.Collections;\nimport java.util.Enumeration;\n\nimport org.apache.catalina.Container;\nimport org.apache.catalina.Context;\nimport org.apache.catalina.Lifecycle;\nimport org.apache.catalina.LifecycleListener;\nimport org.apache.catalina.core.StandardHost;\nimport org.apache.catalina.startup.ContextConfig;\nimport org.apache.catalina.startup.UserConfig;\nimport org.apache.catalina.startup.UserDatabase;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class UserConfigTest {\n\n    @TempDir\n    Path homeBase;\n\n    @Test\n    void deploysUserDirectoryWithConfiguredDatabaseContextAndContextConfigClasses() throws Exception {\n        Path userHome = Files.createDirectories(homeBase.resolve(StaticUserDatabase.USER));\n        Path publicHtml = Files.createDirectories(userHome.resolve(\"public_html\"));\n        Files.writeString(publicHtml.resolve(\"index.html\"), \"user web application\");\n\n        UserConfig userConfig = new UserConfig();\n        userConfig.setHomeBase(homeBase.toString());\n        userConfig.setUserClass(StaticUserDatabase.class.getName());\n        userConfig.setContextClass(\"org.apache.catalina.core.StandardContext\");\n        userConfig.setConfigClass(\"org.apache.catalina.startup.ContextConfig\");\n\n        StandardHost host = new StandardHost();\n        host.setName(\"localhost\");\n        host.setStartChildren(false);\n        host.addLifecycleListener(userConfig);\n\n        try {\n            host.start();\n\n            Container child = host.findChild(\"/~\" + StaticUserDatabase.USER);\n            assertThat(child).isInstanceOf(Context.class);\n            Context context = (Context) child;\n            assertThat(context.getPath()).isEqualTo(\"/~\" + StaticUserDatabase.USER);\n            assertThat(context.getDocBase()).isEqualTo(publicHtml.toString());\n            assertThat(context.findLifecycleListeners()).anyMatch(ContextConfig.class::isInstance);\n        } finally {\n            stopAndDestroy(host);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void stopAndDestroy(StandardHost host) throws Exception {\n        try {\n            if (host.getState().isAvailable()) {\n                host.stop();\n            }\n        } finally {\n            host.destroy();\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class StaticUserDatabase implements UserDatabase {\n\n        static final String USER = \"alice\";\n\n        private UserConfig userConfig;\n\n        @Override\n        public UserConfig getUserConfig() {\n            return userConfig;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void setUserConfig(UserConfig userConfig) {\n            this.userConfig = userConfig;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public String getHome(String user) {\n            return userConfig.getHomeBase() + '/' + user;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Enumeration<String> getUsers() {\n            return Collections.enumeration(Collections.singleton(USER));\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2362, "output": 1333, "cacheRead": 26112, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29807, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781868875040, "responseId": "resp_06093e8c5a67ae81016a35294cb68881909e341b39bdcf02df"}}
